	("LOC_TRAIT_CIVILIZATION_INDUSTRIAL_REVOLUTION_DESCRIPTION",             "[ICON_Resource_Iron] Iron and [ICON_Resource_Coal] Coal Mines +1 [ICON_Production] Production and accumulate 2 more resources per turn. +25% building speed towards Industrial Zone and its buildings. Industrial Zone and Buildings in the Industrial Zone provide +2 [ICON_PRODUCTION] Production and +2 [ICON_SCIENCE] Science."),
	-- 拖船英
	("LOC_LEADER_VICTORIA_ORIGINAL_NAME",                                    "Victoria (Age of Britain)"),
	("LOC_TRAIT_LEADER_PAX_BRITANNICA_NAME",                                 "The Age of Britain"),
	("LOC_TRAIT_CIVILIZATION_PAX_BRITANNICA_EXPANSION2_DESCRIPTION",         "Constructing any Royal Navy Dockyard grants you a copy of the strongest naval unit you can build. Naval Melee unit can escort units with it move at the same speed. Whenever you recruit a [ICON_GREATGENERAL] Great General, gain 1 [ICON_ENVOY] envoy. Increases [ICON_TRADEROUTE] Trade Route capacity by 1 each time a Royal Navy Dockyard district or buildings inside a Royal Navy Dockyard District is constructed in your [ICON_CAPITAL] Capital. Gain the Redcoat unique unit when the Military Science technology is researched."),
	-- 蒸英
